         <abstract>
            <p>This article examines the use of the Voyager CD AudioStack™ to provide HyperCard stacks designed to promote language learning with the ability to play on command precisely specified portions of off-the-shelf audio compact discs in a CD-ROM drive. Four German and Russian HyperCard stacks that benefit directly from the on-line availability of large amounts of digital audio are described and their construction is outlined.</p>
         </abstract>
